The terminal is the interface to the console that you can type and execute text based commands. And you want to use one so you have direct access to the underlying operating system.
Hypertext Transfer Protocol or HTTP and the inventor of it is Tim Berners-Lee. He made it in 1991
client means having access to computers, smartphones and tablets. A server is  a piece of computer hardware or software program that gives funcionality for other programs or devices. A request is a message from the client to the server to retrieve something and the response is the server fufilling the request and sending it to the client
